Odaily Planet Daily News: Nigel Farage, leader of the British Reform Party, will release a Donald Trump-style cryptocurrency policy plan at the Bitcoin Conference, trying to attract more support from young British voters. Nigel Farage will announce that if the British Reform Party wins the next British general election, it will submit a new "Cryptocurrency Bill" to Parliament, with the goal of making the UK a "crypto powerhouse". It is reported that the Hong Kong bill includes: 
The capital gains tax on crypto investments will be significantly reduced from the current 24% to 10%; 
The establishment of a two-year regulatory sandbox to help the City of London innovate in cryptocurrencies; 
Prohibit restrictions on related services that accept crypto payments, thereby protecting the rights of consumers using cryptocurrencies. (Bloomberg)
